</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>AB520:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="AB520"/><meta name="dc:title" content="AB &#xA;              520-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Assembly Bill
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 520</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Castillo<br/>(Coauthors: Assembly Members DeMaio, Essayli, and Macedo)<br/>(Coauthor: Senator Choi)<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>February 10, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> An act to add Article 6 (commencing with Section 12490) to Chapter 5 of Part 2 of Division 3 of Title 2 of the Government Code, relating to public social services. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">AB 520, as introduced, Castillo.
                          Homelessness and mental health: state funding information.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Existing law provides funding for homelessness prevention and mental health services through various state programs, such as Housing First, and the Early Psychosis Intervention Plus Program. Existing law establishes the State Department of Health Care Services and, among other things, requires the department to implement certain mental health services through contracts with a county or counties acting jointly. Existing law requires the Governor to create a California Interagency Council on Homelessness to serve as a statewide facilitator, coordinator, and policy development resource on ending homelessness in California, among other things. Existing law requires the council to create a statewide data system with a goal of matching data on homelessness to programs impacting homeless recipients of state programs.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This bill would require the
		Controller, by January 1, 2027, in collaboration with the department and the council to develop, publish, and maintain an online search portal that contains specified information relating to state funding for programs as described above. The bill would require the portal to include funding amounts provided in the current fiscal year and the previous 10 fiscal years, as well as specified information about the state program that received the funds and the department or agency that administers the program. The bill would require the Controller, the department and the council to each include a link to the online portal on their internet websites. The bill would authorize the Controller, the department and the portal to request any relevant information from a state agency or department for the purpose of reporting accurate information within the portal.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="vote">
      Vote:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">MAJORITY</span>  </span><span id="appropriation">
      Appropriation:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">YES</span>  </span><span id="localprogram">
      Local Program:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><div id="bill"><div style=" text-transform: uppercase"><h2 style=" text-align: left;">The people of the State of California do enact as follows:</h2><br/></div><div id="s10.9556960227940106"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0" class="ActionLine"><h3 style="font-weight:bold; display:inline;">SECTION 1.</h3> Article 6 (commencing with Section 12490) is added to Chapter 5 of Part 2 of Division 3 of Title 2 of the Government Code, to read:</div><div><div><div id="id_BFD80611-22ED-4651-9527-7BFC3CFB12F7"><div><h5 style="text-align:left;">
                Article
               6. Homelessness and Mental Health Funding Information </h5></div></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">12490.</h6> By January 1, 2027, the Controller, in collaboration with the State Department of Health Care Services and the California Interagency Council on Homelessness, shall develop, publish, and maintain an online search portal that contains the information described in subdivisions (a) and (b). The Controller, the State Department of Health Care Services, and the California Interagency Council on Homelessness shall each provide a link to this online portal readily available on their internet websites. The following information shall be made available:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(a) (1) The total amount of funding distributed, per fiscal year, by the Controller’s office for programs and services associated with homelessness and the prevention of homelessness.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) The Controller shall list the total funding amounts distributed for homelessness for the previous 10 fiscal years in conjunction with the current fiscal year.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The Controller shall make apparent the differences in funding levels between fiscal years.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) A searchable and itemized listing of all programs and services that received funding by the Controller for addressing and preventing homelessness in the current fiscal year. Each listing shall include, but not be limited to, the following information:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) The name of the state program that received the funds and the department or agency that administers the program.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The objective or mission of the program.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(C) The amount distributed to the program by the Controller in the fiscal year.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(D) The amount appropriated by the program in the fiscal year.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(E) A contact email address and telephone number for the program’s liaison.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(F) The date the program becomes active or inactive, if applicable.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) (1) The total amount of funding distributed, per fiscal year, by the Controller’s Office for programs and services associated with mental health.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) The Controller shall list the total funding amounts distributed for mental health for the previous 10 fiscal years in conjunction with the current fiscal year.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The Controller shall make apparent the differences in funding levels between fiscal years.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) A searchable and itemized listing of all programs and services that received funding by the Controller for addressing mental health in the current fiscal year. Each listing shall include, but is not limited to, the following information:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) The name of the state program that received the funds and the department or agency that administers the program.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The objective or mission of the program.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(C) The amount distributed to the program by the Controller in the fiscal year.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(D) The amount appropriated by the program in the fiscal
					 year.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(E) A contact email address and telephone number for the program’s liaison.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(F) The date the program becomes active or inactive, if applicable.</div></p></div><div><p><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;"><h6 style="display:inline;">12492.</h6> The Controller, the State Department of Health Care Services, and the California Interagency Council on Homelessness may request any relevant information from a state agency or department for the purpose of reporting accurate information within the portal.</div></p></div></div></div></div></div></div></body></html>
